The Noctes Atticae is a Representative Work, since it not only refiects perfectly the nature of the subjects (ξ 10) which engaged the attention of the liter-ary men of the second century A.D., but also forcibly depicts the spirit in which their labors were prosecuted. Attention has been called above (ξ 4) to their fondness for the writers of the archaic period of Latin literature. In this regard our author shows him- self a thorough-going child of his time.
